nothing will ever get better.

533
00:49:05.166 --> 00:49:06.166
I think you're right.

534
00:49:08.083 --> 00:49:08.916
From now on.

535
00:49:10.500 --> 00:49:12.458
I'm going to do whatever I want.

536
00:49:14.708 --> 00:49:15.833
I don't give a fuck.

537
00:49:22.416 --> 00:49:23.708
You'll get by without me. right?

538
00:49:25.291 --> 00:49:27.541
Yeah. Why do you say that?

539
00:49:28.375 --> 00:49:29.541
I'm not your sidekick.

540
00:49:30.750 --> 00:49:32.125
When you were getting hazed.

541
00:49:33.083 --> 00:49:34.541
who saved your ass then?

542
00:49:35.333 --> 00:49:36.166
[chuckles]

543
00:49:36.833 --> 00:49:38.791
You cried like a dog. man. [chuckles]

544
00:49:38.875 --> 00:49:41.000
-Your dad's a dog.
-[chuckles]

545
00:49:53.791 --> 00:49:55.708
-Go!
-[grunts. groans]

546
00:49:55.791 --> 00:49:57.291
Shit. there he is. Run!

547
00:49:57.791 --> 00:49:59.791
[tense music playing]

548
00:50:04.750 --> 00:50:05.583
[music stops]

549
00:50:12.708 --> 00:50:13.875
[baby coos]

550
00:50:23.250 --> 00:50:24.083
Get some rest.

551
00:50:24.958 --> 00:50:25.875
I'll take over.

552
00:50:34.666 --> 00:50:36.750
[chuckling] Hey there.

553
00:50:36.833 --> 00:50:38.500
Who's Daddy's little baby?

554
00:50:38.583 --> 00:50:40.458
Hey. [chuckling]

555
00:50:40.541 --> 00:50:41.666
Oh. what are you doing?

556
00:50:42.583 --> 00:50:44.791
Oh. is that a big smile for me. huh?

557
00:50:45.666 --> 00:50:47.541
[inhales] Mm.

558
00:50:52.416 --> 00:50:54.333
If we go to the doctor next time…

559
00:50:56.666 --> 00:50:58.333
and they say she needs surgery…

560
00:51:03.291 --> 00:51:04.708
She's just so tiny.

561
00:51:06.875 --> 00:51:08.458
I feel so sorry for her.

562
00:51:11.375 --> 00:51:12.208
[sniffles]

563
00:51:14.791 --> 00:51:16.958
Another debt collection letter came today.

564
00:51:17.041 --> 00:51:18.250
TOTAL: 4.000.135.27 BAHT

565
00:51:18.333 --> 00:51:20.166
We're four payments behind now.

566
00:51:21.041 --> 00:51:22.458
Are we okay. Kong?

567
00:51:24.791 --> 00:51:26.000
[sighs]

568
00:51:29.166 --> 00:51:30.000
I'll handle it.

569
00:51:31.125 --> 00:51:33.250
It's cool. [sniffles softly]

570
00:51:39.375 --> 00:51:41.208
[sniffles. sighs]

571
00:51:46.750 --> 00:51:48.250
[cell phone vibrating]

572
00:51:51.833 --> 00:51:52.666
Hello?

573
00:51:57.041 --> 00:51:57.916
Okay.

574
00:52:04.125 --> 00:52:05.583
The chief's called a meeting.

575
00:52:09.916 --> 00:52:11.000
You need to be there.

576
00:52:22.000 --> 00:52:23.916
[sniffles] Mm.

577
00:52:25.500 --> 00:52:28.958
This is the scene inside after the fire
at Madam Pin's gambling den.

578
00:52:29.958 --> 00:52:31.875
She's an important woman in this town.

579
00:52:32.958 --> 00:52:36.541
It's an illegal operation.
A few times. we've shut it down.

580
00:52:37.416 --> 00:52:39.333
Last time was just three months ago.

581
00:52:40.250 --> 00:52:42.625
But we've never had enough evidence
to link her to it.

582
00:52:44.166 --> 00:52:47.041
We managed to pull
the CCTV hard drives every time.

583
00:52:48.041 --> 00:52:49.166
Including this time.

584
00:52:49.958 --> 00:52:52.708
[clears throat] I'll try to be direct.

585
00:52:54.541 --> 00:53:00.291
The last inspector and other officers
were transferred due to this place.

586
00:53:02.208 --> 00:53:03.958
Now that I've been appointed here.

587
00:53:04.958 --> 00:53:07.083
I'm not letting this affect my good name.

588
00:53:08.250 --> 00:53:09.833
I won't tolerate corruption.

589
00:53:12.041 --> 00:53:15.083
And if I find out
any officers are on the take.

590
00:53:15.166 --> 00:53:16.500
I'll have their head.

591
00:53:18.458 --> 00:53:19.833
I want this handled fast.

592
00:53:20.666 --> 00:53:23.083
Bring me whoever's
really running this place.

593
00:53:24.166 --> 00:53:25.000
Yeah. go.

594
00:53:27.125 --> 00:53:29.458
We've captured this footage near there.

595
00:53:30.791 --> 00:53:31.666
This guy…

596
00:53:31.750 --> 00:53:33.541
Uh. there. Here.

597
00:53:34.708 --> 00:53:37.416
I know this one. His name is Num.

598
00:53:38.583 --> 00:53:41.750
He used to work for Madam Pin.
but he just got out of prison.

599
00:53:41.833 --> 00:53:45.333
He did ten years for murder
after a debt collection went wrong.

600
00:53:45.916 --> 00:53:48.583
When he was caught.
he refused to rat out anyone.

601
00:53:49.708 --> 00:53:51.291
Is he working for Madam Pin this time?

602
00:53:51.791 --> 00:53:53.750
I can't be sure about that.

603
00:53:55.333 --> 00:53:56.333
Uh. keep going.

604
00:53:57.166 --> 00:53:58.875
From the footage. it looks like…

605
00:54:00.083 --> 00:54:03.000
it looks like these hoodlums
are after Num as well.

606
00:54:03.916 --> 00:54:04.750
Oh.

607
00:54:05.500 --> 00:54:08.083
And the old woman who burned to death.

608
00:54:09.250 --> 00:54:12.208
Num was the one who brought her in
to file a report. She said.

609
00:54:12.291 --> 00:54:13.291
She said

610
00:54:13.791 --> 00:54:15.958
she'd been attacked by Po's thugs.

611
00:54:16.041 --> 00:54:19.000
Po is Madam Pin's son.
during a debt collection.

612
00:54:19.958 --> 00:54:22.541
You need to bring in
this Num guy very soon.

613
00:54:23.541 --> 00:54:24.708
-And. Khem…
-Sir.

614
00:54:25.333 --> 00:54:27.291
-Get a team watching Madam Pin.
-Yes. sir.

615
00:54:27.916 --> 00:54:29.625
If there's any connection at all.

616
00:54:30.500 --> 00:54:32.208
Num will bring us straight to her.

617
00:54:33.333 --> 00:54:34.333
Yes. Inspector.

618
00:54:38.833 --> 00:54:39.791
[gasps softly]

619
00:54:43.583 --> 00:54:44.583
[groans softly]

620
00:55:06.500 --> 00:55:08.250
{\an8}BLAZE ENGULFS SHOPHOUSE
CHARRED BODY FOUND

621
00:55:08.333 --> 00:55:11.333
{\an8}-[reporter] <i>They came to collect a debt…</i>
-[Ou] Boss. there's three of them.

622
00:55:11.416 --> 00:55:14.375
-What are you doing in there. Ou?
-There's three in the house. One's hurt.

623
00:55:14.458 --> 00:55:17.625
[woman] <i>People saw what happened.</i>
<i>but they don't dare speak up.</i>

624
00:55:17.708 --> 00:55:18.791
{\an8}<i>Everyone's scared.</i>

625
00:55:18.875 --> 00:55:20.833
[reporter] <i>But the debt dies</i>
<i>with the debtor.</i>

626
00:55:20.916 --> 00:55:22.375
<i>Why would they go that far. ma'am?</i>

627
00:55:23.041 --> 00:55:26.416
[woman] <i>It's to make an example</i>
<i>so no one dares skip a payment.</i>

628
00:55:26.500 --> 00:55:28.375
<i>Why do people still borrow from them?</i>

629
00:55:29.416 --> 00:55:31.708
<i>People here live hand-to-mouth.</i>

630
00:55:31.791 --> 00:55:35.500
{\an8}<i>The banks aren't going to lend them money.</i>
<i>so they go to loan sharks.</i>

631
00:55:36.083 --> 00:55:37.458
<i>But the interest is brutal.</i>

632
00:55:37.541 --> 00:55:40.208
<i>And if you can't pay.</i>
<i>what do you think happens?</i>

633
00:55:40.291 --> 00:55:43.083
<i>You end up like this.</i>
<i>And the police know about it.</i>

634
00:55:43.166 --> 00:55:45.750
<i>-They do nothing…</i>
-Who's this old bitch? I'll find her.

635
00:55:45.833 --> 00:55:47.416
And I'll make sure she pays.

636
00:55:47.500 --> 00:55:49.291
Po. Po. hey.

637
00:55:49.375 --> 00:55:51.541
The guy who hit the den.
I found out where he's hiding.

638
00:55:56.375 --> 00:55:58.375
[soft suspenseful music playing]

639
00:56:25.250 --> 00:56:26.166
You're awake.

640
00:56:28.500 --> 00:56:29.750
When did you get out?

641
00:56:32.208 --> 00:56:33.833
I'd expect that you would visit.

642
00:56:35.666 --> 00:56:36.875
I've been out for a while.

643
00:56:42.500 --> 00:56:43.541
I'm so sorry.

644
00:56:44.333 --> 00:56:45.791
I really should have visited.

645
00:56:49.958 --> 00:56:50.958
What's going on?

646
00:56:52.250 --> 00:56:53.833
I'm always here if you need it.

647
00:56:56.333 --> 00:56:57.291
It's Po.

648
00:57:02.416 --> 00:57:04.166
He burned down someone's house.

649
00:57:05.083 --> 00:57:06.166
Burned them alive.

650
00:57:08.458 --> 00:57:09.458
A kid and her gran.

651
00:57:14.333 --> 00:57:15.666
I was taking care of them.

652
00:57:24.458 --> 00:57:25.375
Come with me.

653
00:58:05.958 --> 00:58:10.750
After what happened at the boxing gym.
I had someone get it out of there.

654
00:58:11.791 --> 00:58:13.208
I've been keeping it safe.

655
00:58:14.250 --> 00:58:15.875
waiting for you to come back for it.

656
00:58:26.916 --> 00:58:29.416
{\an8}I've always loved you like one of my own.

657
00:58:31.583 --> 00:58:33.666
{\an8}You put your life on the line for me.

658
00:58:35.041 --> 00:58:36.375
{\an8}I thank you for that.

659
00:58:37.916 --> 00:58:41.833
{\an8}From now on.
I'll always look after your welfare.

660
00:58:43.958 --> 00:58:46.083
{\an8}Come stay with me. won't you. Num?

661
00:58:52.166 --> 00:58:53.750
In regards to Po.

662
00:58:55.458 --> 00:58:57.500
I'll make sure he apologizes.

663
00:59:01.291 --> 00:59:03.666
He needs to learn from his mistakes.

664
00:59:07.708 --> 00:59:09.208
{\an8}Let's put this behind us.

665
00:59:10.333 --> 00:59:11.166
{\an8}All right?

666
00:59:21.750 --> 00:59:22.791
I'm sorry. ma'am.

667
00:59:23.958 --> 00:59:24.791
[engine starts]

668
00:59:25.458 --> 00:59:27.083
[revving]

669
00:59:51.125 --> 00:59:51.958
[Po] Mom.

670
00:59:52.666 --> 00:59:53.583
Where is he?

671
00:59:57.833 --> 00:59:58.666
He's gone.

672
01:00:01.083 --> 01:00:03.958
Did you really burn down
a debtor's house and kill them?

673
01:00:05.666 --> 01:00:08.625
I thought I said
"don't do anything reckless"?

674
01:00:11.375 --> 01:00:13.541
That bitch went to the cops
so I had to act.

675
01:00:14.416 --> 01:00:16.041
Because. I had to…

676
01:00:16.125 --> 01:00:18.125
make them see they can't get away with it.

677
01:00:18.208 --> 01:00:21.333
What made you think
you should be out there collecting?

678
01:00:22.416 --> 01:00:25.083
You already have
plenty of men to manage that.

679
01:00:26.083 --> 01:00:29.041
Because I'm their boss. I'm their leader.

680
01:00:29.125 --> 01:00:32.333
Because I have to prove
I'm the real deal. so they'll follow.

681
01:00:35.958 --> 01:00:38.875
If Dad was alive. he would back me up.

682
01:00:40.250 --> 01:00:42.791
Your father worked the same way exactly.

683
01:00:43.666 --> 01:00:45.375
and he was killed for doing that.

684
01:00:52.666 --> 01:00:53.916
You love it. don't you?

685
01:00:55.166 --> 01:00:58.708
Shooting your mouth off.
being the big time gangster.

686
01:00:58.791 --> 01:01:01.916
Flexing your power
and pissing everywhere like a dog.

687
01:01:02.458 --> 01:01:05.708
But I'm the one
who has to clean up all your mess.

688
01:01:07.125 --> 01:01:09.083
It's such a massive headache.

689
01:01:12.625 --> 01:01:15.583
The guy who's hunting you down.
his name's Num.

690
01:01:16.250 --> 01:01:18.083
He was once one of mine.

691
01:01:19.208 --> 01:01:20.041
Huh?

692
01:01:20.625 --> 01:01:22.291
This bastard knows I'm your son?

693
01:01:23.750 --> 01:01:26.791
That's shit. Thinks he's
John Wick or something.

694
01:01:27.833 --> 01:01:29.666
If I see him again. I'll fuck him up.

695
01:01:30.291 --> 01:01:31.791
But Num is the real deal.

696
01:01:34.333 --> 01:01:37.250
When he came to work for me.
he was just a kid.

697
01:01:37.333 --> 01:01:39.708
He grew up to be the best in his field.

698
01:01:40.833 --> 01:01:42.458
He was reliable and tough.

699
01:01:43.708 --> 01:01:47.875
If anyone reneged on their debts.
Num was the man.

700
01:01:47.958 --> 01:01:49.916
And people would always relent.

701
01:01:54.000 --> 01:01:54.833
[grunts]

702
01:01:56.166 --> 01:01:58.458
[woman screaming]

703
01:02:04.041 --> 01:02:05.791
[sobbing]

704
01:02:32.291 --> 01:02:34.750
-[gun clatters]
-[woman sobbing]

705
01:02:34.833 --> 01:02:38.166
[Madam Pin] <i>He didn't move an inch</i>
<i>until the police came and took him away.</i>

706
01:02:43.875 --> 01:02:45.750
Num grew up without parents.

707
01:02:47.166 --> 01:02:51.333
For him. that meant
kids are the line you do not cross.

708
01:02:57.125 --> 01:03:00.458
The young child that you burnt
and the old lady that you killed.

709
01:03:01.541 --> 01:03:03.333
you know. Num was their protector.

710
01:03:07.500 --> 01:03:09.208
You need to keep a low profile.

711
01:03:11.041 --> 01:03:13.000
Don't go parading around.

712
01:03:13.083 --> 01:03:15.625
I'll send you to lie low in Cambodia.

713
01:03:15.708 --> 01:03:18.208
When I've cleared up
this mess. you can come back.

714
01:03:21.250 --> 01:03:23.666
[cooing]

715
01:03:58.083 --> 01:03:59.666
[sighs] How's it going?

716
01:04:00.708 --> 01:04:03.750
{\an8}Nothing yet.
Those bastards are being careful.

717
01:04:06.916 --> 01:04:10.041
{\an8}Ah. Here. here. here.
This guy's called Jod.

718
01:04:10.125 --> 01:04:12.541
{\an8}He's ex-military. Special forces.

719
01:04:13.166 --> 01:04:16.541
His record's particularly bloody.
He can't feel pain.

720
01:04:16.625 --> 01:04:18.166
It's a condition of some sort.

721
01:04:18.250 --> 01:04:22.250
Even when a bunch of gamblers swarmed him
and buried a machete in his head.

722
01:04:22.333 --> 01:04:24.375
he just kept swinging
like nothing happened.

723
01:04:24.458 --> 01:04:27.166
This guy. he's a straight up
freak of nature.

724
01:04:27.250 --> 01:04:29.250
[soft suspenseful music playing]

725
01:04:54.208 --> 01:04:55.375
[radio chirps]

726
01:04:55.458 --> 01:04:58.375
[officer] <i>Dispatched to all units.</i>
<i>man fitting Num's description.</i>

727
01:04:58.458 --> 01:05:01.875
<i>Suspect on a red and white motorcycle</i>
<i>at Ratchadamri intersection.</i>

728
01:05:01.958 --> 01:05:03.125
<i>Heading into town. Over.</i>

729
01:05:03.958 --> 01:05:07.041
-I got this one.
-Hey. hey. hey. Hey!

730
01:05:14.375 --> 01:05:16.375
{\an8}[indistinct chatter]

731
01:05:40.208 --> 01:05:42.208
[engine revs]

732
01:05:42.291 --> 01:05:44.291
-Hey!
-[tense music playing]

733
01:05:52.583 --> 01:05:55.000
[honking]

734
01:05:58.583 --> 01:06:01.333
Hey! Pull over! Pull over. Now!

735
01:06:04.416 --> 01:06:06.083
-Hey!
-[screeches]

736
01:06:07.375 --> 01:06:09.291
Ah. fuck! Fuck! Shit!

737
01:06:11.375 --> 01:06:14.083
[clamoring]

738
01:06:17.500 --> 01:06:19.250
[tires screech]

739
01:06:39.291 --> 01:06:41.041
[truck honks]

740
01:06:41.125 --> 01:06:43.166
[muffled screeching]

741
01:06:45.791 --> 01:06:47.041
[crashes]

742
01:07:01.375 --> 01:07:03.750
Num! [panting]

743
01:07:05.125 --> 01:07:06.458
Hey. stop.

744
01:07:07.208 --> 01:07:08.333
[grunts]

745
01:07:09.500 --> 01:07:11.250
-Stop!
-[panting]

746
01:07:11.333 --> 01:07:12.291
Hey. Num!

747
01:07:12.958 --> 01:07:14.541
[panting]

748
01:07:20.666 --> 01:07:21.625
Hey. Num!

749
01:07:22.458 --> 01:07:23.583
It's Kong. man!

750
01:07:26.166 --> 01:07:28.208
We were in Saengtawan together.

751
01:07:32.416 --> 01:07:34.625
You smashed Mr. Tom's face.

752
01:07:37.958 --> 01:07:39.666
We parted by the river.

753
01:07:39.750 --> 01:07:41.083
Remember. man?

754
01:07:46.708 --> 01:07:48.791
And I was the guy on the pier.

755
01:07:49.625 --> 01:07:51.666
You know. the one you threw in the water.

756
01:07:56.208 --> 01:07:57.791
Turn yourself in.

757
01:07:59.625 --> 01:08:01.166
It'll all be all right.

758
01:08:05.083 --> 01:08:07.041
[Num] I just need to deal with Po.

759
01:08:09.041 --> 01:08:11.500
When that's done. I'll turn myself in.

760
01:08:14.708 --> 01:08:16.000
[leaves rustling]

761
01:08:16.083 --> 01:08:18.833
Hey. stop! Num. stop!

762
01:08:20.583 --> 01:08:22.250
Num. stop!

763
01:08:22.333 --> 01:08:25.000
-Num! Num!
-[panting]

764
01:08:26.458 --> 01:08:28.166
Stop! Num!

765
01:08:28.958 --> 01:08:30.458
-Hold it!
-[gunshot]

766
01:08:31.625 --> 01:08:34.916
[Num panting]

767
01:08:39.458 --> 01:08:41.833
[unsettling music plays]

768
01:08:47.500 --> 01:08:49.875
[Kong panting]

769
01:08:50.750 --> 01:08:51.583
Num?

770
01:08:53.291 --> 01:08:54.125
Num!

771
01:09:09.958 --> 01:09:10.791
Hello?

772
01:09:12.000 --> 01:09:13.416
I'm bringing in Num.

773
01:09:14.291 --> 01:09:15.791
-[grunts]
-[groans]

774
01:09:15.875 --> 01:09:17.916
[choking]

775
01:09:18.000 --> 01:09:19.458
[groans]

776
01:09:22.166 --> 01:09:24.000
-You piece of shit!
-[grunts in pain]

777
01:09:24.083 --> 01:09:25.666
-You bastard!
-[grunts in pain]

778
01:09:26.375 --> 01:09:27.625
-Tough guy?
-[groans]

779
01:09:28.541 --> 01:09:30.000
[muffled grunt]

780
01:09:31.083 --> 01:09:32.375
[Num coughs]

781
01:09:32.458 --> 01:09:33.750
Give me the gun.

782
01:09:36.750 --> 01:09:38.125
God damn it. give me the gun!

783
01:09:38.208 --> 01:09:39.416
Po!

784
01:10:09.041 --> 01:10:11.500
As requested. four million.

785
01:10:21.625 --> 01:10:23.666
[grunting]

786
01:10:47.250 --> 01:10:48.666
[engine revving]

787
01:10:53.916 --> 01:10:55.208
[tires squeal]

788
01:11:27.958 --> 01:11:30.791
[intense dramatic music plays]

789
01:12:41.958 --> 01:12:43.000
[Kong groans]

790
01:12:44.083 --> 01:12:45.166
[grunts]

791
01:12:50.875 --> 01:12:51.958
[Kong panting]

792
01:12:52.041 --> 01:12:53.500
[retches]

793
01:12:54.625 --> 01:12:57.333
[gasps. coughing]

794
01:13:02.583 --> 01:13:03.875
[pants heavily]

795
01:13:05.583 --> 01:13:07.208
[both pant]

796
01:13:11.500 --> 01:13:12.750
[Num grunts]

797
01:13:18.916 --> 01:13:20.000
[coughs]

798
01:13:21.708 --> 01:13:22.875
Hey. Num?

799
01:13:23.416 --> 01:13:25.083
Num. I'm sorry.

800
01:13:26.875 --> 01:13:28.166
[Num sighs]

801
01:13:29.958 --> 01:13:31.291
I'm drowning in debt.

802
01:13:34.625 --> 01:13:37.041
I co-signed a loan for a cop friend.

803
01:13:38.416 --> 01:13:39.958
He bailed on it.

804
01:13:41.208 --> 01:13:43.000
And now I'm paying it back.

805
01:13:46.875 --> 01:13:48.041
I'm trapped.

806
01:13:49.250 --> 01:13:50.250
I'm sorry.

807
01:13:59.541 --> 01:14:01.291
[unsettling music plays]

808
01:14:01.375 --> 01:14:02.458
-[groans]
-Hey. Num!

809
01:14:07.625 --> 01:14:09.125
[door opens]

810
01:14:10.958 --> 01:14:12.083
[exhales]

811
01:14:16.958 --> 01:14:19.500
Hey. This is a work friend.

812
01:14:20.500 --> 01:14:21.791
Could you leave us?

813
01:14:56.375 --> 01:14:58.500
You should stay here for now.

814
01:15:03.958 --> 01:15:05.291
Hey. Num.

815
01:15:06.791 --> 01:15:08.041
Turn yourself in.

816
01:15:08.666 --> 01:15:11.250
You'd be a lot safer in police custody.

817
01:15:12.250 --> 01:15:13.708
Sure about that?

818
01:15:15.375 --> 01:15:17.083
Do you feel protected?

819
01:15:21.916 --> 01:15:23.000
Kong?

820
01:15:24.041 --> 01:15:25.416
Sergeant Khem called.

821
01:15:26.125 --> 01:15:27.750
He said he couldn't reach you.

822
01:15:43.000 --> 01:15:44.125
Hello. sir?

823
01:15:48.375 --> 01:15:49.791
I'm okay. yeah.

824
01:15:52.000 --> 01:15:59.000
PING PING

825
01:16:00.250 --> 01:16:03.500
I lost track of Num just.
uh. outside town.

826
01:16:04.500 --> 01:16:05.500
Yep.

827
01:16:11.375 --> 01:16:13.083
Don't worry about me.

828
01:16:13.166 --> 01:16:15.166
[suspenseful music playing]

829
01:16:17.416 --> 01:16:18.541
Okay.

830
01:16:47.958 --> 01:16:50.458
[foreboding music playing]

831
01:16:58.500 --> 01:17:00.916
[abbot] Are you here
to pray for something else?

832
01:17:06.125 --> 01:17:08.958
Your sinful ways aren't worth revisiting.

833
01:17:10.583 --> 01:17:12.541
It's too late. Father.

834
01:17:15.000 --> 01:17:18.208
No. it's not. You were on the way.

835
01:17:20.083 --> 01:17:21.958
You mustn't lose faith.

836
01:17:23.500 --> 01:17:24.833
Have mercy.

837
01:17:25.625 --> 01:17:27.333
Forgive and let go.

838
01:17:28.791 --> 01:17:31.041
{\an8}If I end up forgiving them.

839
01:17:32.833 --> 01:17:34.708
when do I get revenge?

840
01:17:37.666 --> 01:17:40.416
{\an8}I know how this is supposed to end.

841
01:17:44.666 --> 01:17:47.791
Using violence is never the solution.

842
01:17:51.041 --> 01:17:53.625
It's the only way I've ever known. Father.

843
01:17:56.791 --> 01:17:58.333
[abbot] Take time to think.

844
01:17:58.416 --> 01:18:00.166
Reflect on yourself.

845
01:18:01.166 --> 01:18:03.083
<i>Your body is failing.</i>

846
01:18:03.916 --> 01:18:05.875
<i>and your mind is growing weak.</i>

847
01:18:06.625 --> 01:18:08.041
<i>Get some rest.</i>

848
01:18:08.541 --> 01:18:09.791
<i>Trust me.</i>

849
01:18:10.500 --> 01:18:13.125
<i>There's an empty hut behind the temple.</i>

850
01:18:18.041 --> 01:18:19.250
Go. go.

851
01:18:49.541 --> 01:18:51.041
[gun firing]

852
01:18:54.291 --> 01:18:55.375
[thug] Hey. Po!

853
01:18:56.000 --> 01:18:57.083
Po!

854
01:18:57.166 --> 01:18:58.333
[Po] What is it?

855
01:19:01.291 --> 01:19:02.125
Hello?

856
01:19:05.583 --> 01:19:06.708
Are you sure?

857
01:19:10.666 --> 01:19:13.333
That bastard Num. he's still alive.

858
01:19:16.791 --> 01:19:17.916
Where are you?

859
01:19:19.791 --> 01:19:23.333
If you kill him. you get 100.000.

860
01:19:26.625 --> 01:19:27.750
Damn it!

861
01:19:38.375 --> 01:19:40.083
[exhales. sniffles]

862
01:19:40.875 --> 01:19:42.000
Hello. sir.

863
01:19:45.041 --> 01:19:46.125
[sighs]

864
01:19:50.666 --> 01:19:53.333
If everything you've just told me is true.

865
01:19:54.458 --> 01:19:55.791
you'll be charged as well.

866
01:19:56.500 --> 01:19:57.541
You know that.

867
01:20:05.333 --> 01:20:06.541
I understand.

868
01:20:08.791 --> 01:20:09.958
[Kong sighs]

869
01:20:11.208 --> 01:20:13.000
Anyone else know about it?

870
01:20:18.208 --> 01:20:19.250
No. sir.

871
01:20:19.958 --> 01:20:22.125
You're the only one that I would tell.

872
01:20:23.333 --> 01:20:24.458
Why is that?

873
01:20:25.125 --> 01:20:27.375
Do you think I'll help you cover it up?

874
01:20:31.000 --> 01:20:32.166
No. sir.

875
01:20:33.208 --> 01:20:35.416
If I'm wrong. I'll pay for it.

876
01:20:36.166 --> 01:20:38.250
I just want to set things right.

877
01:20:39.333 --> 01:20:42.166
I just don't want them
to hurt anyone else.

878
01:20:44.708 --> 01:20:46.250
I want this over.

879
01:21:00.625 --> 01:21:02.541
Some higher-ups have called.

880
01:21:03.208 --> 01:21:04.416
They want me to drop this.

881
01:21:07.875 --> 01:21:09.333
But I'm not doing it.

882
01:21:11.083 --> 01:21:12.875
They pull this one all the time.

883
01:21:14.625 --> 01:21:16.916
But I have my own way of operating.

884
01:21:18.750 --> 01:21:20.291
And importantly.

885
01:21:21.500 --> 01:21:24.958
I'm after someone on my side to help out.

886
01:21:30.750 --> 01:21:32.125
Can I trust you?

887
01:21:36.083 --> 01:21:37.416
[exhales]

888
01:21:38.375 --> 01:21:39.333
You can.

889
01:21:40.666 --> 01:21:41.541
Thanks.

890
01:21:43.166 --> 01:21:45.041
If you do find anything.

891
01:21:45.583 --> 01:21:47.541
you should report it to me alone.

892
01:21:48.125 --> 01:21:50.541
As for the brass. I'll handle them.

893
01:21:51.958 --> 01:21:52.791
Yeah.

894
01:21:58.041 --> 01:22:00.750
[gagging and coughing]

895
01:22:00.833 --> 01:22:01.833
[strains]

896
01:22:03.500 --> 01:22:06.666
[gasps. coughs]

897
01:22:18.166 --> 01:22:20.166
[foreboding music plays]

898
01:22:26.000 --> 01:22:28.250
[breathing heavily]

899
01:22:32.541 --> 01:22:34.333
[footsteps approaching]

900
01:22:38.833 --> 01:22:40.750
[breathing heavily]

901
01:22:54.583 --> 01:22:56.583
[sinister music plays]

902
01:22:59.291 --> 01:23:03.375
[monitor beeping]

903
01:23:05.708 --> 01:23:07.583
[monitor flatlining]

904
01:23:08.791 --> 01:23:11.083
Why didn't you come and save me?

905
01:23:11.166 --> 01:23:13.583
[girl screams]

906
01:23:15.458 --> 01:23:17.791
[shuddering breaths]

907
01:23:26.083 --> 01:23:28.083
[unsettling music plays]

908
01:23:39.625 --> 01:23:41.625
[breathing heavily]

909
01:23:48.791 --> 01:23:49.875
[thuds]

910
01:23:49.958 --> 01:23:52.958
[breathing rapidly]

911
01:23:53.041 --> 01:23:54.083
[gun clicks]

912
01:23:56.291 --> 01:23:58.500
[breathing rapidly]

913
01:23:58.583 --> 01:23:59.750
[gun clicks]

914
01:24:02.958 --> 01:24:04.750
[gasps. then shouts]

915
01:24:05.791 --> 01:24:06.958
-[gunshot]
-[exclaims]

916
01:24:07.916 --> 01:24:09.375
-[Num grunts]
-Fuck it.

917
01:24:09.458 --> 01:24:10.625
You bastard!

918
01:24:11.708 --> 01:24:12.708
[grunts]

919
01:24:13.791 --> 01:24:15.041
[gunshot]

920
01:24:15.750 --> 01:24:18.500
[breathing heavily]

921
01:24:21.333 --> 01:24:23.541
[panting]

922
01:24:32.958 --> 01:24:36.083
-[dogs barking]
-[animal howling]

923
01:24:36.166 --> 01:24:37.333
[gun clicks]

924
01:24:43.666 --> 01:24:45.375
The abbot's waiting for you.

925
01:25:16.083 --> 01:25:17.291
[meows]

926
01:26:01.333 --> 01:26:03.500
[man] Hello? Is that the police?

927
01:26:03.583 --> 01:26:05.583
I'd like to report a body.

928
01:26:05.666 --> 01:26:07.500
ALL CREATURES ARE GOVERNED
BY THEIR OWN KARMA

929
01:26:07.583 --> 01:26:09.583
If all creatures are ruled by karma.

930
01:26:11.666 --> 01:26:14.250
then. Father. tell us.

931
01:26:14.333 --> 01:26:16.166
how should this creature pay?

932
01:26:18.875 --> 01:26:19.750
Father.

933
01:26:20.708 --> 01:26:24.208
If you help him. that means
you've taken on this man's karma.

934
01:26:27.791 --> 01:26:30.458
We each have a karmic debt to come.

935
01:26:31.750 --> 01:26:33.333
Even living as a monk.

936
01:26:34.041 --> 01:26:36.500
my life also has to conform.

937
01:26:40.458 --> 01:26:42.000
Speaking of debt.

938
01:26:42.750 --> 01:26:44.541
this temple owes me.

939
01:26:45.875 --> 01:26:49.208
My family name's all over it
because we paid for its construction.

940
01:26:52.458 --> 01:26:54.750
Yet instead of being thankful.

941
01:26:55.333 --> 01:26:56.833
you turn on us.

942
01:26:58.583 --> 01:27:00.916
It's not too late to stop. Po.

943
01:27:04.750 --> 01:27:06.541
Don't add to your kar--

944
01:27:06.625 --> 01:27:07.958
[thuds]

945
01:27:08.541 --> 01:27:09.708
-Hey! Whoa!
-[Num grunts]

946
01:27:21.500 --> 01:27:23.500
-[Num grunts]
-Hold him down.

947
01:27:23.583 --> 01:27:26.083
-Hold him down.
-[grunting angrily]

948
01:27:27.333 --> 01:27:28.958
[Num groaning]

949
01:27:29.041 --> 01:27:30.291
[coughs]

950
01:27:32.958 --> 01:27:34.250
[straining]

951
01:27:36.666 --> 01:27:38.458
[footsteps approaching]

952
01:27:40.833 --> 01:27:43.208
[Num grunts]

953
01:27:44.458 --> 01:27:47.833
Do you remember? Huh? Huh?

954
01:27:53.666 --> 01:27:54.833
-[gunshot]
-Huh?

955
01:27:58.958 --> 01:28:00.333
-[gunshots]
-[grunts]

956
01:28:00.875 --> 01:28:03.416
Move it! Move! Get up!

957
01:28:04.666 --> 01:28:06.166
[Num shudders]

958
01:28:10.041 --> 01:28:12.291
-[Num grunts]
-Num. move!

959
01:28:19.875 --> 01:28:22.041
Num. come on! Move!

960
01:28:22.125 --> 01:28:23.291
[gunshots]

961
01:28:28.083 --> 01:28:30.000
-[thug 1] Go after them!
-[thug 2] Let's go.

962
01:28:30.083 --> 01:28:30.916
[thug 3] This way!

963
01:28:32.125 --> 01:28:33.166
Damn it!

964
01:28:42.208 --> 01:28:43.916
[tool whirring]

965
01:28:44.875 --> 01:28:47.041
[car honking]

966
01:28:47.125 --> 01:28:48.750
[engine revving]

967
01:28:49.708 --> 01:28:51.750
[honking continues]

968
01:28:55.708 --> 01:28:57.125
[thug 1] Move. move!

969
01:28:59.458 --> 01:29:01.083
-[thug 1] Out of the way!
-[thug 2] Move!

970
01:29:01.166 --> 01:29:02.500
[thug 3] Move! Hurry!

971
01:29:02.583 --> 01:29:04.666
[crowd screaming]

972
01:29:05.541 --> 01:29:06.541
[grunts]

973
01:29:14.708 --> 01:29:17.250
[thug 4] Hey. stop him! Move it!

974
01:29:19.750 --> 01:29:20.625
[grunts]

975
01:29:24.083 --> 01:29:25.583
[people clamoring]

976
01:29:28.333 --> 01:29:29.750
-[man exclaims]
-[grunts]

977
01:29:30.916 --> 01:29:32.708
[upbeat music playing over speakers]

978
01:29:42.416 --> 01:29:43.833
[motor revving]

979
01:29:47.875 --> 01:29:50.208
[upbeat music playing]

980
01:29:50.291 --> 01:29:51.208
Hey!

981
01:29:52.083 --> 01:29:54.000
[motor revving]

982
01:29:55.166 --> 01:29:56.583
[tires squeal]

983
01:30:13.916 --> 01:30:15.333
-[crashes]
-[yelps]

984
01:30:16.750 --> 01:30:18.083
[crowd screaming]

985
01:30:20.333 --> 01:30:22.583
-[gasps]
-[children screaming]

986
01:30:24.541 --> 01:30:26.041
[Kong] Hey. out of the way!

987
01:30:26.125 --> 01:30:27.791
[crowd screaming]

988
01:30:46.833 --> 01:30:48.791
[low tense music playing]

989
01:31:16.625 --> 01:31:18.125
Hey. don't move!

990
01:31:18.833 --> 01:31:19.958
Drop the gun.

991
01:31:32.791 --> 01:31:34.208
[grunts]

992
01:31:36.166 --> 01:31:37.791
[pants]

993
01:31:43.458 --> 01:31:44.458
[shouts]

994
01:31:48.083 --> 01:31:49.333
[grunts]

995
01:31:52.791 --> 01:31:54.208
[strains. grunts]

996
01:31:57.416 --> 01:32:01.250
[groaning]

997
01:32:03.041 --> 01:32:04.041
[groans]

998
01:32:05.458 --> 01:32:06.666
[groans]

999
01:32:08.458 --> 01:32:10.083
[groaning]

1000
01:32:13.875 --> 01:32:15.166
[shouts]

1001
01:32:21.500 --> 01:32:22.958
[panting]

1002
01:33:02.541 --> 01:33:03.541
[grunts]

1003
01:33:13.333 --> 01:33:15.125
[straining]

1004
01:33:16.291 --> 01:33:18.541
[groans. coughs]

1005
01:33:24.250 --> 01:33:25.666
[coughs]

1006
01:33:26.833 --> 01:33:27.791
[grunts]

1007
01:33:28.875 --> 01:33:29.958
[groans]

1008
01:33:31.541 --> 01:33:33.041
[both grunting]

1009
01:33:57.083 --> 01:33:58.375
[groaning]

1010
01:34:03.333 --> 01:34:04.666
[loud thud]

1011
01:34:05.416 --> 01:34:07.166
[muffled grunt]

1012
01:34:10.291 --> 01:34:11.333
[strains]

1013
01:34:13.458 --> 01:34:15.166
[muffled grunting]

1014
01:34:18.916 --> 01:34:21.375
-[loud thud]
-[breathing heavily]

1015
01:34:22.916 --> 01:34:24.333
[Num coughs. grunts]

1016
01:34:24.916 --> 01:34:27.125
[Num groans. then coughs]

1017
01:34:42.208 --> 01:34:43.250
[yelps]

1018
01:34:48.708 --> 01:34:49.875
[Kong grunts]

1019
01:34:52.875 --> 01:34:54.250
[Num pants]

1020
01:34:54.333 --> 01:34:55.458
[thuds]

1021
01:34:56.625 --> 01:34:58.666
[panting]

1022
01:35:01.625 --> 01:35:03.791
[Kong coughing]

1023
01:35:03.875 --> 01:35:05.041
[Num groans]

1024
01:35:13.958 --> 01:35:15.291
[Kong coughs]

1025
01:35:18.875 --> 01:35:20.541
[indistinct clamor]

1026
01:35:23.166 --> 01:35:24.000
Num!

1027
01:35:29.583 --> 01:35:31.500
[car starting]

1028
01:35:35.458 --> 01:35:37.708
-[coughing]
-Hey. Num!

1029
01:35:50.458 --> 01:35:52.916
Boss. let's go.

1030
01:35:55.250 --> 01:35:56.291
Shit!

1031
01:36:02.625 --> 01:36:04.833
EMERGENCY PATIENT DROP-OFF

1032
01:36:04.916 --> 01:36:07.625
[Kong] I need help here.
Could you help me. please?

1033
01:36:11.250 --> 01:36:12.166
Hurry!

1034
01:36:16.083 --> 01:36:17.125
[grunts]

1035
01:36:17.208 --> 01:36:18.916
[cell phone line ringing]

1036
01:36:21.958 --> 01:36:24.250
Mom. Jod's dead.

1037
01:36:26.083 --> 01:36:28.958
[Madam Pin] <i>Don't come home.</i>
<i>Go into hiding.</i>

1038
01:36:29.041 --> 01:36:31.708
<i>Once I've arranged</i>
<i>how to get you out. I'll come for you.</i>

1039
01:36:31.791 --> 01:36:33.041
Okay.

1040
01:36:37.625 --> 01:36:39.208
Hey. get in.

1041
01:36:48.041 --> 01:36:49.541
[cell phone vibrating]

1042
01:36:54.125 --> 01:36:55.375
Hello. Inspector.

1043
01:36:55.458 --> 01:36:56.708
[Inspector Tong] <i>Where are you?</i>

1044
01:36:57.500 --> 01:36:58.625
[sighs]

1045
01:36:59.625 --> 01:37:01.375
You know all about the temple.

1046
01:37:01.458 --> 01:37:04.583
[Inspector Tong] <i>I do.</i>
<i>Come to my place now.</i>

1047
01:37:04.666 --> 01:37:07.375
<i>We'll plan Madam Pin's takedown tonight.</i>

1048
01:37:09.208 --> 01:37:10.208
Yes. sir.

1049
01:37:30.166 --> 01:37:31.041
Yes.

1050
01:37:32.708 --> 01:37:33.583
Yes. sir.

1051
01:37:35.125 --> 01:37:36.708
We're close on our end.

1052
01:37:37.250 --> 01:37:39.500
I'll let you know
as soon as there's progress.

1053
01:37:40.958 --> 01:37:41.916
Yes.

1054
01:37:43.750 --> 01:37:44.750
Yes. sir.

1055
01:37:54.208 --> 01:37:56.250
We got the green light to go for Pin.

1056
01:38:01.625 --> 01:38:05.333
My men have told me.
you helped Num get away.

1057
01:38:06.458 --> 01:38:07.291
Why?

1058
01:38:12.083 --> 01:38:13.958
He's my friend. Inspector.

1059
01:38:15.625 --> 01:38:17.000
We lived in an orphanage.

1060
01:38:18.041 --> 01:38:19.833
Ten years ago. perhaps.

1061
01:38:21.708 --> 01:38:23.250
We reconnected over…

1062
01:38:24.250 --> 01:38:25.166
over this.

1063
01:38:27.750 --> 01:38:30.041
Why haven't you told me this before?

1064
01:38:35.791 --> 01:38:37.333
Where is he now?

1065
